<%# Shared sidebar/topbar/footer chrome for both consoles (Admin, SuperAdmin) — ported from the
    webadmin template's pages-starter.html vertical-layout variant (requirement.md §5.14; see
    vendor/webadmin_template/pages-starter.html for the source). Only the vertical sidebar layout
    is used; the template's alternate horizontal-topbar markup and its theme-customizer right
    sidebar (RTL/dark-mode/layout-switcher demo controls) are intentionally not ported — this is a
    product, not a template showcase. Sidebar collapse + MetisMenu init are Stimulus-controlled
    (app/javascript/controllers/sidebar_controller.js) instead of loading the template's app.js
    wholesale, which assumes demo-only DOM we don't ship.

    Rendered via `render layout: "shared/console_shell", locals: { ... } do ... end` from
    layouts/admin.html.erb and layouts/super_admin.html.erb — the block becomes `yield` below,
    i.e. the actual page content. Locals:
      home_path            — user_root_path / platform_staff_root_path — no bare root_path exists,
                              every route carries its console's /admin or /platform namespace
                              (config/routes.rb)
      nav_items           — Array of { path:, icon:, label: } — see app/helpers/{admin,super_admin}_helper.rb
      footer_text          — String, e.g. "EventMeet" / "EventMeet Platform"
      user_dropdown        — Hash of locals for shared/_user_dropdown, or nil if signed out

    Topbar shows a static welcome message (ported from shopmate-backend's _upper_header.html.erb,
    same template family) rather than the per-page title — that now lives in the content area
    itself, via shared/_page_header's breadcrumb + <h4> (content_for(:page_title) still drives the
    browser <title> tag, shared/_head.html.erb). %>
<%# data-controller="confirm-dialog" lives here, not per-trigger, so any button anywhere in the
    page content can use a plain data-action="click->confirm-dialog#show" (see
    shared/_confirm_dialog.html.erb) without redeclaring it — Stimulus resolves an action to the
    nearest ancestor carrying the matching data-controller, same as data-action="sidebar#toggle"
    below already relies on this element for the sidebar controller. %>
<div id="layout-wrapper" data-controller="sidebar confirm-dialog">
  <%# class="isvertical-topbar" — load-bearing, not decorative: app.min.css positions
      #page-topbar via `.isvertical-topbar{position:fixed;left:270px;...}` (offset past the
      fixed-position sidebar's own width). Without it the topbar renders at its static in-flow
      position instead, landing underneath/behind the sidebar — invisible, not just misplaced.
      Confirmed against both the original template mockup (vendor/webadmin_template/
      pages-starter.html) and shopmate-backend's own _header.html.erb, which both carry this
      class; missing here since Phase 0, undetected until real topbar content (the page-title
      text, now shared/_page_header's breadcrumb) made the occlusion visible. %>
  <header id="page-topbar" class="isvertical-topbar">
    <div class="navbar-header">
      <div class="d-flex">
        <div class="navbar-brand-box">
          <%= render "shared/brand_link", home_path: home_path %>
        </div>

        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm px-3 font-size-24 header-item waves-effect" data-action="sidebar#toggle">
          <i class="bx bx-menu align-middle"></i>
        </button>

        <div class="page-title-box align-self-center d-none d-md-block">
          <h4 class="page-title mb-0">Welcome back!</h4>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="d-flex">
        <%= render "shared/user_dropdown", **user_dropdown if user_dropdown %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="vertical-menu">
    <div class="navbar-brand-box">
      <%= render "shared/brand_link", home_path: home_path %>
    </div>

    <div class="sidebar-menu-scroll">
      <div id="sidebar-menu">
        <ul class="metismenu list-unstyled" id="side-menu" data-sidebar-target="menu">
          <li class="menu-title">Menu</li>
          <% nav_items.each do |item| %>
            <li>
              <%= link_to item[:path], class: "waves-effect" do %>
                <i class="bx <%= item[:icon] %> icon nav-icon"></i> <span class="menu-item"><%= item[:label] %></span>
              <% end %>
            </li>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="main-content">
    <div class="page-content">
      <div class="container-fluid">
        <%= yield %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6">&copy; <%= Date.current.year %> <%= footer_text %>.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "shared/flash" %>
<%= render "shared/confirm_dialog" %>
